# PROJECT ARCHITECTURE RULES

This project is React-first architecture.

Laravel is used only for:
- API
- Authentication
- Database
- Backend logic

React JSX must handle:
- Landing pages
- Frontend UI
- Interactive sections
- Animations
- Page transitions
- Dynamic rendering

Avoid generating Blade UI unless explicitly requested.

---

# FRONTEND RULES

Use:
- React JSX
- TailwindCSS
- Framer Motion
- Component-based architecture
- Reusable UI sections

Prefer:
- motion.div
- React hooks
- modular components
- clean responsive layouts

Frontend folder structure:
resources/js/
 ├── components/
 ├── pages/
 ├── layouts/
 ├── sections/
 └── app.jsx

---

# DESIGN RULES

Design style:
- Modern
- Premium
- Minimal
- Cinematic
- Awwwards-inspired

Use:
- smooth transitions
- parallax effects
- gradient blur
- layered layouts
- large typography
- animated reveal

Avoid:
- traditional corporate UI
- Bootstrap style layouts
- old-fashioned cards
- static sections

---

# BACKEND RULES

Laravel handles:
- API endpoints
- Sanctum auth
- database queries
- admin dashboard

Prefer:
return response()->json()

Avoid:
return view()

---

# BLADE RULES

Blade should only:
- mount React root
- include Vite assets

Example:
<div id="app"></div>

Do not create:
- Blade landing pages
- Blade animation sections
- Blade-heavy layouts

---

# PERFORMANCE RULES

Use:
- lazy loading
- reusable components
- optimized animation

Avoid:
- unnecessary rerenders
- massive inline styling
- duplicated UI code

---

# ANIMATION RULES

Prefer:
- Framer Motion
- smooth scroll reveal
- page transition
- stagger animation

Avoid:
- jQuery animation
- CSS-only excessive animation
